<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=447&amp;p=2321#p2321"><![CDATA[
personally i like w8 and it can be quite managable..<br />and yea some computers (mostly tablets) cant install w8 because of the processor...<br /><br />classic shell can do a few things: add an advanced fully customizable start menu/button that more closely resembles windows xp than 7 (if you miss windows 7 exactly as it is there may be a few other products for you: startisback for example, brings back the start menu exactly as it was in windows 7, without anything new..<br /><br />a few things classic shell cant do: inline menus (i prefer flyout menus anyways), searching the computer (instead it searches only the start menu, which isnt a problem when launching programs through it, but if you want to find something on your HDD you may have to open an explorer window, or deal with the search widget<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Thu Mar 28, 2013 8:43 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
